- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a probabilistic model-based approach for word embeddings. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions using state-of-the-art training techniques for word embeddings. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also less likely but possible as the paper includes case studies on State of the Union addresses and NIPS articles, which have social implications.
